ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to create/insert requirements(s) and/or update the contents of existing requirement occurrences.

Operation.description: This operation creates child occurrences of SpecElement type and its subtypes to a selected parent RequirementSpec or inserts new SpecElement occurrence(s) after a specified selected sibling occurrence or updates the contents of existing requirement occurrence(s). Creation, insertion or updation requires the parent RequirementSpec to be viewed and edited in CKEditor, which is visible when the parent occurrence is opened in documentation tab of ACE panel in edit mode. Updated or newly created requirement occurrences are saved in HTML format and are rendered in HTML viewer in the documentation tab.
Operation.name: createOrUpdateContents
Operation.returnDescription:
If successful, ServiceData containing newly created objects is returned.
If an error occurs then ServiceData will contain partial error.
The following partial errors may be returned:
141023: The object has been modified. Please refresh the object before editing.
159008: The object can not be added as it is not a supported type.
159001: An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module. Please report this error to your system administrator.
Operation.useCase:
Use Case 1: Create a new Requirement occurrence as a child of an empty Requirement Specification parent
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title in documentation tab. On clicking the "new requirement" button icon of the CKEditor toolbar, a widget appears in the text area, with regions for content, title and a requirement icon. Inside the "Title" content control, user types-in the name of new SpecElement occurrence. Clicking on "Content" with right mouse button, requirement types appear. User selects any of the available types by clicking on the type. Beneath the Content type, user writes in the content inside a content controller, which is the Body Text of the new requirement. After adding this new requirement, clicking on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, the new requirement is saved in HTML format.

Use Case 2: Insert new requirement(s) after a specific requirement occurrence
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title alongwith the children requirement inside the edit area of CKEditor. User selects the content of one of the intermediate requirements inside the editor. User then clicks on "new requirement" button icon of the CKEditor toolbar. A widget appears in the text area, with regions for content, title and icon beneath the previously selected requirement content. User adds multiple such requirements in this way. After inserting the new requirement(s), user clicks on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, resulting into saving of the new requirement(s) in HTML format.

Use Case 3: Update content of existing requirement(s)
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and then navigates to documentation tab. User clicks on "Start Edit" option present in the toolbar. This loads CKEditor (HTML editor) inside the documentation tab. The Requirement Specification name is rendered as a title alongwith the children requirement inside the edit area of CKEditor. User selects the content of one of the intermediate requirements inside the editor. User then edits the content by adding/deleting text in content controller. User can add multiple such requirements in this way. After updating the content(s) the requirement(s), user clicks on "Save" button in AWC toolbar, resulting into updating of the body text for this requirement(s) in HTML format.

Use Case 4: Insert new requirement occurrence(s) and edit contents of existing occurrence(s)
User performs operations mentioned in use case #2 and use case #3 in a single edit session followed by a subsequent save. All the newly added requirement occurrences(s) are saved and the edited contents of existing requirement(s) are updated in HTML format.

ParameterInfo.description: A  list of structure which holds the file meta data, format of the document,  type of specification elements to be created.

Operation.description:
This operation imports a Requirement Specification document containing SpecElement objects. It creates Requirement or Paragraph objects and associated data (FullText for each created Item to store the contents from the document and IMAN_Specification relation between FullText and each created SpecElement). The input structure for this operation contains file meta data information, type of specification elements (SpecElement) to be created, application format of the MS Word document being imported, keyword parsing options to be used during import, live or static import mode to be used for import, option to import as new specification or under the selected BOMLine object and description to be set on the SpecElement once imported.

If the application format is "MSWordXML" then the operation parses the given MSWord document to creates a structure of type SpecElement.
If the application format is "MSWordXMLExisting" then the given MSWord document is imported to Teamcenter to create a Specification within an existing chosen Specification.
Operation.name: importFromWord
Operation.returnDescription:
A list of created objects. The following partial error may be returned:
    • 223519 Invalid Input object type, the supported input object types are Folder and Awb0Element type.
    • 223520 Invalid application format, the supported application formats are MSWordXML and MSWordXMLExisting.
    • 223521 Invalid specification element type. Supported type are subtype of SpecElement.
    • 223522 Invalid specification type. Supported type are RequirementSpec and subtype of RequirementSpec.
    • 46147 Cannot add the child to the selected parent since this child type is not valid for parent type.
    • 46180 The child cannot be added to the selected parent since the parent type is not valid for the child type.
Operation.useCase:
1) User selects a folder and clicks on the “Import” button in ActiveWorkspace import panel and imports the MSWord file. If user choose "Import as Specification", the requirements will be created under a specification and the specifiation will be saved into the folder.

2) User select an Awb0Element element in ActiveWorkspace ACE view and clicks on the “Import” button in import panel. If user chooses Import as requirements (Not in a Specification), requirements will be created as children of the Awb0Element element.

ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to move the selected occurrences within the structure.

Operation.description:
This operation allows the user to moves the selected occurrences in the structure.

Following are supported values for input operation argument.

1. Move up - This input operation provides the capability of moving the selected occurrence up within the same parent hierarchy.

2. Move down- This input operation provides the capability of moving the selected occurrence down within the same parent hierarchy.

3. Promote- This input operation provides the capability of moving the selected occurrence to its grand parent within the same structure.

4. Demote- This input operation provides the capability of moving the selected occurrence as a child of the immediate sibling above the selected occurrence.
Operation.name: moveSelectedOccurrences
Operation.returnDescription:
The updated occurrence after the movement of selected occurrence within the structure.
The following partial errors may be returned:
126001 An internal error has occurred in the Occurrence Management module.
126002 No Adapter could be found to handle the Product. The system has not been adequately enhanced or customised to deal with the data given to it as input.
126012 The selected input object is not an BusinessObject of type Awb0Element.
Operation.useCase:
1) User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure. User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the MoveUp button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence up within the same parent hierarchy
2) User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure. User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the MoveDown button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence down within the same parent hierarchy.
3) User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure. User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the Promote button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence to its grand parent within the structure.
4) User loads a structure in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. The ACE panel is used for smart navigation of occurrences in a structure. User selects an occurrence in the structure and clicks on the Demote button in the command bar. This action will move the selected occurrence as a child of the immediate sibling above the selected occurrence.

ParameterInfo.description: Input for the operation to create or update the derived Requirement Specification.

Operation.description: This operation creates a duplicate of the existing selected Requirement Specification and also provides an option to create a derived Requirement Specification. Derived Requirement Specification will be readonly copy and it has the same contents as the original Requirement Specification.Any changes done in the original Requirement Specification wll refer to the derived Requirement Specification. Based on the inputs, the element in the derived Specification can be freezed, unfreezed or overwriten. If derived Requirement is frozen, then the source can continue to modify the content, but derived Requirement will not get new changes and will continue to see older content. If derived Requirement is unfreezed then the latest changes from the original Requirement will be shown. If the derived Requirement is overwritten then it will have a new copy and there will be no link between the master and derived Requirement after overwrite.
Operation.name: reuseSpecification
Operation.returnDescription:
If successful, the newly created Requirement Specification object will be returned along with the ServiceData. If an error occurs then ServiceData will contain partial error.
The following partial errors may be returned:

159001 - An internal error has occurred in the Requirements Management module. Please report this error to your system administrator.
159008 - The object can not be derived as it is not a supported type.
Operation.useCase:
Use Case 1: Create a new copy of Requirement Specification
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. User clicks on “Reuse” command which shows the “Reuse and Derived” panel. User selects “Create a new copy of Specification” and selects a tracelink type and clicks on Create button. This creates a new copy of the existing Requirement specification.It will deep copy the objects from the original Requirement Specification. Each Requirement which is duplicated will have a tracelink with the original Requirement.

Use Case 2: Create Derived Requirement Specification
User loads the requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel. User clicks on “Reuse” command which shows the “Reuse and Derived” panel. User selects “Create a derived Specification” and selects a tracelink type and clicks on Create button. This creates a derived of the existing Requirement specification.It will deep copy the objects from the original Requirement Specification except for the FullText dataset. Each Requirement which is duplicated will have a tracelink with the original Requirement. Any changes to the contents of original Requirement Specification will reflect automatically in the derived Requirement Specification.

Use Case 3: Freeze Derived Requirement
User loads the derived requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and navigates to “Documentation” tab. From the side bar panel in Documentation tab, user clicks on “Freeze” command. After this action source Requirement can continue to modify the content, but derived Requirement will not get new changes and will continue to see older content.

Use Case 4: Unfreeze Derived Requirement
User loads the derived requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and navigates to “Documentation” tab. From the side bar panel in Documentation tab, user clicks on “Unfreeze” command. After this action derived requirement will refer to Fulltext dataset version on latest revision of source Requirement and subsequent changes to the source requirement content will be reflect in the derived Requirement.

Use Case 5: Overwrite Derived Requirement
User loads the derived requirement specification in ACE (Active Content Experience) panel and navigates to “Documentation” tab. From the side bar panel in Documentation tab, user clicks on “Overwrite” command. After this action derived requirement will refer to new Fulltext dataset version and subsequent changes to the source requirement content will not reflect in the derived Requirement.

OperationTemplate.description:
This operation imports a Requirement Specification document containing SpecElement objects. It creates Requirement or Paragraph objects and associated data (FullText for each created Item to store the contents from the document and IMAN_Specification relation between FullText and each created SpecElement). The input structure for this operation contains file meta data information, type of specification elements (SpecElement) to be created, application format of the MS Word document being imported, keyword parsing options to be used during import, live or static import mode to be used for import, option to import as new specification or under the selected BOMLine object and description to be set on the SpecElement once imported.

If the application format is "MSWordXML" then the operation parses the given MSWord document to creates a structure of type SpecElement.
If the application format is "MSWordXMLExisting" then the given MSWord document is imported to Teamcenter to create a Specification within an existing chosen Specification.
OperationTemplate.name: Arm0::Soa::ActiveWorkspaceReqMgmt::ImportExport::importFromWordAsync
OperationTemplate.returnDescription: This is an asynchronous method, there is no return value.

OperationParameter.description: inputData
OperationParameter.name: inputData

OperationTemplate.description: Imports an Excel file into Teamcenter and creates the Requirement structure and sets the properties on objects based on the values given in Excel file. The input Excel file contains a level column to indicate the level of the object in the structure. "Level" and "Object Type" columns are mandatory in the input Excel sheet. The input Excel file is parsed to import the data to create Requirement structure in Teamcenter. This operation supports creation of objects only. Update and Delete are not supported.
OperationTemplate.name: Arm0::Soa::ActiveWorkspaceReqMgmt::ImportExport::importSpecificationFromExcel
OperationTemplate.returnDescription:
The column headers and property information after parsing the input file and a ServiceData element. The following partial errors may be returned.
    • 223508: Updating an existing structure is not supported.
    • 223509: The selected input file does not have mandatory columns "Tc_Level" and "Tc_ObjectType".
    • 223510 The header information in the selected input file does not match with the mapping input data.
    • 223511 The input type provided contains required properties which are not supplied in the input Excel file.
    • 223512 The input type provided contains MFK properties which are not supplied in the input Excel file.
